_Balkanalysis.com_
[writes](http://www.balkanalysis.com/macedonia/2011/03/12/in-skopje-
macedonian-jewish-legacy-commemorated-with-events-and-new-holocaust-memorial-
center/) about the Holocaust Memorial Center opening ceremony, held in the
capital of Macedonia on March 11: “Even though things will never be as they
once were in a country where little more than 200 Jews survive, at least for a
moment one could feel something of what the culturally richer Skopje of old
must have been like.” The Center, located “on the site of Skopje’s former
Jewish quarter,” is a “$23-million complex” that houses “an impressive three
floors of exhibits, multi-media presentations and historical information […].”

